  "body": "### Version of Hardhat\n\n2.14.0\n\n### What happened?\n\n`hardhat-chai-matchers` doesn't extend with `chai-as-promised` types when pnpm is used as package manager.\r\n\r\nThe matchers are being added as tests behave as expected when run (runs successfully as hardhat uses typescript transpile-only flag) but it causes issues with type checking in IDEs\r\n\n\n### Minimal reproduction steps\n\n1. Create new hardhat project\r\n3. Install `hardhat-chai-matchers`\r\n4. Run `pnpm install`\r\n5. Use a `chai-as-promised` assertion (such as `expect(transaction).to.be.fulfilled`)\n\n### Search terms\n\n_No response_",
